   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Fourteen REAL FREEDOM Scripture: John 8:32, 34, 36</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Today everybody talks about freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Now we will see what real freedom is.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>All they that sin are the slaves of sin The slave is under bondage, having no freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Everyone who commits sin is the slave of sin, under the bondage of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Today those who talk about freedom are, in fact, the slaves of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The high class educationalist and the intellectuals all are the slaves of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Playing chess, smoking, dancing, and being under the bondage of various habits are the symptoms of being the slaves of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Real Freedom The inability to escape from sin reveals the lack of freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The ability to escape from sin shows the real freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Today many do not have the real freedom because of the bondage and oppression of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Many are aware of the bondage of sin and seek for deliverance, but are unable to achieve it.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Therefore there is no freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The real freedom means the absence of the condemnation of the conscience and deliverance from the bondage of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The real freedom is dependent on the Lord The Lord is truth.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Only He can cause men to know the reality of human life.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Only He can cause men to know the mystery of human life.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Only He can cause men to know God, and God is the source of freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To bear the sins of men, the Lord died and rose again from the dead.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>So He is able to forgive men s sins.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>He also can deliver men from their sins.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>His blood brings in the forgiveness of sin and sets men free from the condemnation of the conscience.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The Lord s life enables men to escape from the bondage of sin, so there is the real freedom.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>How to be free Whoever wants to be free has to confess that he is the slave of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>He must also receive the Lord and His salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>In His salvation are blood and life.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>His blood provides for the forgiveness of men s sins, and His life enables men to be delivered from the bondage of sin.</S>
   </TEXT>
